Game Instructions:
1. User will input number based on if they want PvP(1) or PvAI(2)
2. In order to make a move on the board, user will input valid x and y positions to determine which piece you intend to move
3. User will then input a x and y position for where they wish to move that piece which was obtained
4. A valid move is one that is not the same colour as the piece you want to move and within the rules of the game of chess
5. Once a valid move is made, the other player will have a chance to make a move of their own (AI or Human pending step one)
6. Game will be checked to see if player has won after every move and will be checked if no more pieces can be moves (ie stalemate/checkmate)

